@import ./_tui.convo

> user
Add first-pass rich text support for inline sprites.

Goals:
- Extend the TUI types to allow inline text with styled spans.
- Support foreground color, background color, and plain text per span.
- Preserve existing `text` behavior for simple sprites.
- Add rendering support for styled inline spans.
- Keep wrapping/clipping behavior consistent with plain text as much as possible.
- Keep the API compact and easy to use.

Acceptance criteria:
- A sprite can render plain `text` exactly as before.
- A sprite can render rich inline content with per-span colors/backgrounds.
- Theme color variables and `#rrggbb` colors work for rich text spans.
- Wrapping and clipping still work for rich text.
- Existing examples/tests continue to work without changes.

Update notes at the end of your response
